Install Niginx and add secure PHPMyAdmin:
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install nginx
  sudo ufw allow 'Nginx Full'
  systemctl status nginx
  
To setup PhpMyAdmin:
  sudo mkdir -p /var/www/phpmyadmin
  wget https://files.phpmyadmin.net/phpMyAdmin/5.0.2/phpMyAdmin-5.0.2-all-languages.zip
  unzip phpMyAdmin-5.0.2-all-languages.zip (and delete Setup folder)
  
To setup a server block:
  sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/pma.supportdedicated.com
  
  Add a server block:
     server {
        listen 80;
        listen [::]:80;

        root /var/www/phpmyadmin;
        index index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;

        server_name supportdedicated.com www.supportdedicated.com;

        location / {
                try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
        }
      }
  
  
To manage Nginx:
  sudo systemctl stop nginx
  sudo systemctl start nginx
  sudo systemctl restart nginx
  sudo systemctl reload nginx
  sudo systemctl disable nginx
  sudo systemctl enable nginx
